  "prompt": "What do yellow roses symbolize?",
  "response": "Yellow roses are rich in symbolism and generally convey positive emotions. They are most commonly associated with friendship, joy, and warmth. Here\u2019s a breakdown of their meanings:\n\n1. **Friendship**: Yellow roses are often given to celebrate and honor close friendships, symbolizing the bond and happiness shared between friends.  \n2. **Joy and Happiness**: Their bright, sunny color evokes feelings of cheerfulness, optimism, and new beginnings.  \n3. **Platonic Love**: Unlike red roses, which symbolize romantic love, yellow roses represent non-romantic, platonic affection.  \n4. **Welcome and Hospitality**: They can also be used to express welcome or to uplift someone\u2019s spirits.  \n\nHistorically, yellow roses were sometimes associated with jealousy or infidelity, but this interpretation has largely faded, and they are now seen as purely positive symbols. When gifting yellow roses, they are often a great choice to show appreciation or celebrate a happy occasion! \ud83c\udf3c",
